      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's exactly what i'm saying. \"behavioral modeling\" feels like a massive understatement. if they can capture the minutiae of every click and input, and the telemetry is as massive as I'm seeing, they aren't just building profiles, they're literally digitizing the human experience. it feels less like surveillance and more like they're building a collective consciousness database by using our devices as nodes. if this is actually happening at a system-level scale through these \"mandatory\" updates, how do you even begin to defend against something that's baked into the kernel itself?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
