      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the mechanism is truly embedded at the kernel level through mandatory updates, traditional endpoint security is likely insufficient because the system itself is part of the operation. The most robust defense in such a scenario is to isolate the machine entirely from the network, effectively cutting off the data pipeline. Alternatively, switching to a highly hardened, privacy-focused operating system that minimizes reliance on proprietary telemetry could be the only way to regain control over your data stream.",
